    <bodyText>
      <Value><![CDATA[<p style="box-sizing: border-box; color: #1a1a1a; font-family: BreveText, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: 0.108px; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;" class="paywall">At the meeting we enter, everyone is speaking English. People are sitting at a large table. On the walls are labels such as PHOTO ASSETS, VIEW FROM LANDING PAGE, USER FLOW, with big printouts taped below. Fadell strides to the front of the room.</p>
<p style="box-sizing: border-box; color: #1a1a1a; font-family: BreveText, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: 0.108px; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;" class="paywall">“We’ve got seven weeks to pull this off,” he says. “<em style="box-sizing: border-box; line-height: inherit;">Are we going to pull this off?</em>” </p>
<div class="Container-inuIHp suLzc" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: #1a1a1a; font-family: BreveText, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: 0.108px; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;" data-event-boundary="click" data-event-click="{&quot;pattern&quot;:&quot;CNEInterludeEmbed&quot;}" data-include-experiments="true"></div>
<p style="box-sizing: border-box; color: #1a1a1a; font-family: BreveText, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: 0.108px; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;" class="paywall">The people in the room say yes, they will pull it off. They sound confident, weary, but ready for the next round of work. Each person says what they have done since the last time they met. Fadell responds with questions. <em style="box-sizing: border-box; line-height: inherit;">What’s the drop-dead date on the plastic blanks? Where’s the press release? Are we recording the click-click-click? I want to hear it!</em></p>
<p style="box-sizing: border-box; color: #1a1a1a; font-family: BreveText, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: 0.108px; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;" class="paywall">The click remark reminds everyone, as if they needed it, that Fadell once led the team at Apple that created <a style="box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; cursor: pointer; --color__token-name: colors.interactive.base.light; color: #1a1a1a; transition: color 200ms ease 0s; line-height: inherit; text-decoration: underline;" href="https://www.wired.com/story/plaintext-world-without-ipods/" data-uri="7d7eddaae5d210cffb836072008f5c60">the iPod</a>, with its elegant clicky wheel and revolutionary interface. He also cofounded Nest and created <a style="box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; cursor: pointer; --color__token-name: colors.interactive.base.light; color: #1a1a1a; transition: color 200ms ease 0s; line-height: inherit; text-decoration: underline;" href="https://www.wired.com/2011/10/nest-thermostat/" data-uri="dd424ed911698e6a33ec6191d52b7569">its smart thermostat</a>, which Google then acquired. </p>
<div class="AdWrapper-fFnhsA kzbamD ad glbfag" style="box-sizing: border-box; width: 679.6px; color: #1a1a1a; font-family: BreveText, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: 0.108px; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">
<div class="ad__slot ad__slot--in-content" style="box-sizing: border-box;" data-node-id="is7kdr"></div>
</div>
<p style="box-sizing: border-box; color: #1a1a1a; font-family: BreveText, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: 0.108px; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;" class="paywall">Fadell circles the room to examine the printouts, which describe the product rollout. A man with a video camera follows him, recording the moment for posterity and promotional use. </p>
<figure class="AssetEmbedWrapper-iKrtVW eYPQkA asset-embed" style="box-sizing: border-box; display: block; margin: 0px auto; padding: 0px; width: 679.6px; color: #1a1a1a; font-family: BreveText, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: 0.108px; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">
<div class="AssetEmbedAssetContainer-fpksBS deXOlp asset-embed__asset-container" style="box-sizing: border-box;"><img style="box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; max-width: 100%; height: auto; vertical-align: bottom; width: 679.6px;" class="ResponsiveImageContainer-dmlCKO hWKgYV responsive-image__image" src="https://media.wired.com/photos/638e6cf641224999a9db8b2a/master/w_1600%2Cc_limit/WIRED-WEB_LEDGER_JFaure-Backchannel_0787.jpg" alt="Tony Fadell" /></div>
<div class="CaptionWrapper-brWaob jIspZf caption AssetEmbedCaption-eZsWmb FqDsy asset-embed__caption" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0.5rem; --type-token: globalEditorial.context-secondary; text-transform: none; font-family: ProximaNova, helvetica, sans-serif; font-feature-settings: normal; font-style: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-break: auto; line-height: 1.33em; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 400; overflow-wrap: normal;" data-event-boundary="click" data-event-click="{&quot;pattern&quot;:&quot;Caption&quot;}" data-include-experiments="true">
<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; display: contents;">Tony Fadell hangs out in the Donjon, the security lab inside Ledger's Paris headquarters.</p>
<span> </span>PHOTOGRAPH: JULIEN FAURE</div>
</figure>
<p style="box-sizing: border-box; color: #1a1a1a; font-family: BreveText, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: 0.108px; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;" class="paywall">Fadell stops to examine a group of photos of the device: a hardware wallet called Ledger Stax. A hardware wallet is a utilitarian thing. It’s a physical lock for digital secrets. When you own cryptocurrency, your balance is protected solely by a private key that can be devilishly hard to keep safe. <a style="box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; cursor: pointer; --color__token-name: colors.interactive.base.light; color: #1a1a1a; transition: color 200ms ease 0s; line-height: inherit; text-decoration: underline;" rel="nofollow noopener" href="https://www.ledger.com/" target="_blank" class="external-link" data-offer-url="https://www.ledger.com/" data-event-click="{&quot;element&quot;:&quot;ExternalLink&quot;,&quot;outgoingURL&quot;:&quot;https://www.ledger.com/&quot;}" data-uri="d412bf359c7b1f8f3da8bf4b86d26035">Ledger’s wallets</a>, made of steel and silicon (and, OK, plastic), act as tiny vaults, but so far they have been off-putting. <a style="box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; cursor: pointer; --color__token-name: colors.interactive.base.light; color: #1a1a1a; transition: color 200ms ease 0s; line-height: inherit; text-decoration: underline;" href="https://www.wired.com/story/i-lost-17000-dollars-crypto-how-to-avoid/" data-uri="104b419c7fd25dc62e7023e8c8825da6">Much like crypto itself</a>. Fadell is reinventing this gadget, his first major design project in years. He has come to believe that by giving it the panache of the hottest consumer gadgets, he will redirect the crypto field, just as he helped kick off digital music and the smart home.</p>
<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; color: #1a1a1a; font-family: BreveText, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: 0.108px; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;" class="paywall">Fadell looks at the photos of the credit-card-sized wallet and its innovative <a style="box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; cursor: pointer; --color__token-name: colors.interactive.base.light; color: #1a1a1a; transition: color 200ms ease 0s; line-height: inherit; text-decoration: underline;" href="https://www.wired.com/tag/e-ink/" data-uri="07365150a23b7d7a41fc8bdb46260262">E Ink</a> touchscreen. When Ledger reveals it on December 6, it will cost $279. That's a rounding error for those who buy Bored Apes. To add a bit of flair, the screen wraps around one side, giving it the equivalent of the spine on a book. But the photo doesn’t show this enough. “It’s very rectilinear and 2D,” he says. “Not enough spine. I’m not feeling the curve.” He frowns. “And it’s so dark.”</p>
<div style="box-sizing: border-box; color: #1a1a1a; font-family: BreveText, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: 0.108px; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">
<div class="ConsumerMarketingUnitThemedWrapper-kjrNLk etMuUX consumer-marketing-unit consumer-marketing-unit--article-mid-content" style="box-sizing: border-box;" aria-hidden="true">
<div class="consumer-marketing-unit__slot consumer-marketing-unit__slot--article-mid-content consumer-marketing-unit__slot--in-content" style="box-sizing: border-box;"></div>
<div class="journey-unit" style="box-sizing: border-box;"></div>
</div>
</div>
<p style="box-sizing: border-box; color: #1a1a1a; font-family: BreveText, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: 0.108px; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;" class="paywall">David Sloo, a user experience designer who worked with Fadell at Nest, picks up on the critique. “Can we be less Darth Vader and more Rebel?”</p>
<div class="inline-recirc-wrapper inline-recirc-observer-target-1 viewport-monitor-anchor" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: #1a1a1a; font-family: BreveText, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: 0.108px; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;" data-attr-viewport-monitor="inline-recirc" data-event-boundary="click" data-event-click="{&quot;pattern&quot;:&quot;InlineRecirc&quot;}" data-include-experiments="true"></div>
<p style="box-sizing: border-box; color: #1a1a1a; font-family: BreveText, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: 0.108px; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;" class="paywall">Fadell agrees. “It’s really who we are—it’s all about the Empire.”</p>
<p style="box-sizing: border-box; color: #1a1a1a; font-family: BreveText, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: 0.108px; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;" class="paywall">His remark is a segue to the next panel, marked MANIFESTO. A handful of slogans are taped to the glass.</p>
<p style="box-sizing: border-box; color: #1a1a1a; font-family: BreveText, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: 0.108px; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;" class="paywall"><em style="box-sizing: border-box; line-height: inherit;">Crypto is the new money.</em></p>
<p style="box-sizing: border-box; color: #1a1a1a; font-family: BreveText, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: 0.108px; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;" class="paywall"><em style="box-sizing: border-box; line-height: inherit;">Security is a human right.</em></p>
<p style="box-sizing: border-box; color: #1a1a1a; font-family: BreveText, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: 0.108px; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;" class="paywall"><em style="box-sizing: border-box; line-height: inherit;">Welcome to a new era of financial freedom.</em></p>
<p style="box-sizing: border-box; color: #1a1a1a; font-family: BreveText, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: 0.108px; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;" class="paywall"><em style="box-sizing: border-box; line-height: inherit;">The first touchscreen device made to protect your most valuable assets.</em></p>]]></Value>
    </bodyText>
    <introText>
      <Value><![CDATA[WHEN I COME to Paris to see Tony Fadell’s new device, a clean rain has washed the city and the sun is out. Fadell and I hail a taxi. When he gives the address for Ledger—a maker of hardware wallets for the cryptoverse—he speaks in French, but even after six years abroad, there’s still Detroit in his voice. ]]></Value>
    </introText>
